The paper deals with the construction and properties of perfect codes over finite fields, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also discusses the switching construction and the Lindstrom-Schonheim construction, which are relevant to cryptography (cs.CR) and coding theory (cs.CC). Finally, the paper provides a lower bound for the number of pairwise distinct perfect codes, which involves numerical analysis (cs.NA).
